"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-08-paris-2024-olympics-lawal-misses-out-on-medal-in-womens-weightlifting\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Nigeria continued her medal drought at the ongoing 2024 Olympic Games with Folashade Rafiatu Lawal missing out on a podium finish in the women's 59kg weightlifting event.  Lawal battled hard but finished in fifth position with a total lift of 230kg in the Snatch; Clean and Jerk.  Her tally was 5kg short of bronze medallist Kuo Hsing-chun of Chinese Taipei.  Earlier in the day, Nigeria failed to advance into the final of 4x100m relays.  The quartet of Favour Ashe, Kanyinsola Ajayi, Alaba Akintola and Usheoritse Itsekiri finished 7th in heat 1 of the men's 4x100m.  Similarly, the quartet of Justina Eyakpobeyan, Favour Ofili, Rosemary Chukwuma and Tima Godbless finished 6th in heat 2 of the women's 4x100m, running a season's best time of 42.70s.  In wrestling, Odunayo Adekuroye lost to China's Kexin Hongin the quarter-finals, while Esose Ibadin failed to earn a place in the men's 800m final.  He's always a competitive animal - Xabi Alonso on Mikel Arteta  Transfer: 'Good luck' - Chelsea announces deal for Aaron Anselmino  Gov Lawal's defection sparks massive APC membership surge in Zamfara  Gov Lawal's defection to APC will development to Zamfara - Shinkafi  2027: Gov Lawal's defection will boost Tinubu's re-election prospects - APC chieftain, Suzuki  New era of reconciliation in Zamfara - Shehu Sani reacts to Gov Lawal's defection  Zamfara: Matawalle welcomes Gov Lawal to APC  APC postpones Zamfara congress amid Gov Lawal's defection rumours  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"